#: .\items.json
msgid "underground map"
msgid_plural "underground maps"
msgstr[0] "地下地图"

#. ~ Use action message for {'str': 'underground map'}.
#: .\items.json
msgid "You add the underground sites to your map."
msgstr "你将地下地点添加到了你的地图上。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'underground map'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"This is a crude map of the local sewers and subways.  It has a few "
"additional sites as well."
msgstr "这是一张当地下水道和地铁的粗略地图。上面还标有一些额外的地点。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "morlock cookbook"
msgid_plural "morlock cookbooks"
msgstr[0] "摩洛克食谱"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'morlock cookbook'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A hand written notebook full of nightmarish Morlock recipes, such as rat "
"soup, cockroach stirfry, worm-in-a-blanket, and others.  But there are a few"
" useful recipes mixed in with the bad."
msgstr "一本手写笔记本，充满了噩梦般的摩洛克食谱，例如鼠肉汤、蟑螂炒菜、毯裹蠕虫等等。但在糟糕的食谱中也混杂着一些有用的。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "mush-tea"
msgid_plural "mush-tea"
msgstr[0] "蘑菇茶"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'mush-tea', 'str_pl': 'mush-tea'}
#: .\items.json
msgid "A healthy beverage made from mushrooms steeped in boiling water."
msgstr "一种健康的饮品，由在沸水中浸泡的蘑菇制成。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "glowing mushroom"
msgid_plural "glowing mushrooms"
msgstr[0] "发光蘑菇"

#. ~ Use action activation_message for {'str': 'glowing mushroom'}.
#: .\items.json
msgid "You eat the magic."
msgstr "你吃下了这魔法。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'glowing mushroom'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A mutated mushroom that gives off a faint phosporescent glow.  Not safe to "
"eat in this state."
msgstr "一种发出微弱磷光的变异蘑菇。在此状态下食用不安全。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "glowing mushroom culture"
msgid_plural "glowing mushroom culture"
msgstr[0] "发光蘑菇培养物"

#: .\items.json
msgid "dried glowing mushroom"
msgid_plural "dried glowing mushrooms"
msgstr[0] "干燥的发光蘑菇"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'dried glowing mushroom'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A mutant mushroom.  It no longers glows with phosphorescent light, but still"
" looks unsafe to eat."
msgstr "一种变异蘑菇。它不再发出磷光，但看起来仍然不安全，不宜食用。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "magic tea"
msgid_plural "magic tea"
msgstr[0] "魔法茶"

#. ~ Use action activation_message for {'str': 'magic tea', 'str_pl': 'magic
#. tea'}.
#: .\items.json
msgid "You drink the magic."
msgstr "你喝下了这魔法。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'magic tea', 'str_pl': 'magic tea'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A healthy beverage made from mutated mushrooms steeped in hot water.  May "
"cause hallucinations."
msgstr "一种健康的饮品，由在热水中浸泡的变异蘑菇制成。可能导致幻觉。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "sunshine mash"
msgid_plural "sunshine mashes"
msgstr[0] "阳光醪"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'sunshine mash', 'str_pl': 'sunshine mashes'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"Unfermented sunshine.  Just some water, sugar, and glowing mutant mushrooms,"
" just like Urist used to make."
msgstr "未发酵的阳光。只是一些水、糖和发光的变异蘑菇，就像乌里斯特过去常做的那样。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "sunshine wash"
msgid_plural "sunshine washes"
msgstr[0] "阳光酒醪"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'sunshine wash', 'str_pl': 'sunshine washes'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"Fermented, but not distilled sunshine.  Contains all the contaminants you "
"don't want in your sunshine."
msgstr "已发酵但未蒸馏的阳光。含有所有你不想在阳光中看到的杂质。"

#: .\items.json
msgid "sunshine"
msgid_plural "sunshine"
msgstr[0] "阳光"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'sunshine', 'str_pl': 'sunshine'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"Only the strongest, purest, good ol' fashioned hooch, distilled from glowing"
" mushrooms and sugar.  The prefered drink of all subterranean people."
msgstr "只有最烈、最纯、老式的好酒，由发光蘑菇和糖蒸馏而成。所有地下居民的首选饮品。"

#: .\items_NPC_missions.json
msgid "Hologram Projector - Locator of Morlock Village"
msgid_plural "Hologram Projector - Locator of Morlock Villages"
msgstr[0] "全息投影仪 - 摩洛克村庄定位器"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Hologram Projector - Locator of Morlock
#. Village'}
#: .\items_NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"This is a hologram projector which generates an interactive hologram when "
"you activate it. Hologram can talk to you, answer some of your questions, "
"but most importantly, it can locate Morlock Village"
msgstr "这是一台全息投影仪，激活后可生成交互式全息影像。全息影像能与你对话，回答部分问题，但最重要的是它能定位莫洛克村的位置。"

#: .\mammal.json
msgid "cave piglet"
msgid_plural "cave piglets"
msgstr[0] "洞穴猪崽"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'cave piglet'}
#. ~ Description for {'str': 'cave pig'}
#: .\mammal.json
msgid ""
"A mutant omnivore descended from the domestic pig.  It has adapted to life "
"underground by losing all skin pigment, going blind, and becoming even less "
"picky about what it eats."
msgstr "由家猪演化而来的突变杂食动物。为适应地下生活，其皮肤完全褪去色素，双目失明，且对食物更加不挑剔。"

#: .\mammal.json
msgid "cave pig"
msgid_plural "cave pigs"
msgstr[0] "洞穴猪"

#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Morlock Village"
msgstr "莫洛克村"

#. ~ Description for Morlock Village
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid ""
"Adds an underground village of mutant NPCs.  Connects to subways and sewers."
msgstr "新增一个由突变NPC构成的地下村落。可连通地铁与下水道系统。"

#: .\overmap_terrain.json
msgid "morlock_village"
msgstr "莫洛克村"

#: .\terrain.json
msgid "giant mushroom"
msgstr "巨型蘑菇"

#. ~ Description for giant mushroom
#: .\terrain.json
msgid "A Terrestrial mushroom that has mutated to an enormous size."
msgstr "一种陆地蘑菇因突变而生长至庞大体型。"

#: .\terrain.json
msgid "crunch!"
msgstr "嘎吱！"

#: .\terrain.json
msgid "whack!"
msgstr "啪！"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Morlock Village Locator Hologram"
msgstr "莫洛克村定位全息仪"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Hologram Protection"
msgstr "全息影像防护"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Hologram Protection'}
#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "\"I am programmed to not engage wandering monsters.\""
msgstr "\"我的程序设定为不与游荡怪物交战。\""

#. ~ Description for mission '{'str': 'Go to Morlock Village'}'
#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Go to Morlock Village"
msgstr "前往莫洛克村"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"You want me to find this location for you to explore? Sure, you will just "
"need to wait for a couple of minutes or less for me to find it via my "
"network system"
msgstr "要我为你定位探索地点？没问题，只需等我用网络系统查找几分钟或更短时间"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"You want me to locate it now for you to explore? Sure, just tell me, you "
"will just need to wait for a couple of minutes or less for me to find it via"
" my network system"
msgstr "你想让我现在为你定位那个地点以便探索吗？当然，告诉我吧，你只需要等几分钟或更短时间，我就能通过网络系统找到它。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Good luck to you!"
msgstr "祝你好运！"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"Not interested in explorations of new locations? No rush hopefully. You can "
"come back to me later. I'm sure that you will. Because I believe that you "
"are not a boring person"
msgstr "对新地点的探索不感兴趣吗？别急，希望如此。你可以稍后再来找我。我相信你会的，因为我觉得你不是个无聊的人。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Use your wits for your own safety hopefully as well"
msgstr "也希望你运用智慧确保自身安全。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Have you went to this location that I have found for you to explore?"
msgstr "你去过我为你找到的那个探索地点了吗？"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Good work!"
msgstr "干得好！"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"What's the point of lying to me? You think I'm gonna reward you? Your "
"rewards for this mission is valuable for you items or living creatures or "
"other survivors you manage to find in this location which I have found for "
"you to explore"
msgstr ""
"对我撒谎有什么意义？你以为我会奖励你吗？这次任务的奖励就是你在那个地点找到的对你来说有价值的物品、生物或其他幸存者，那是我为你找到的探索地点。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"You are a boring, lazy person honestly. I guess that laziness applies to "
"both of us"
msgstr "说实话，你是个无聊又懒惰的人。我想懒惰这一点我们俩都适用。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"System is online. Initiate conversation mode. Look at that. Survivor has "
"managed to activate a hologram projector easily! Yeah, my creators know many"
" types of you who don't even read what's written on items honestly. Good "
"that you seem like a pretty intelligent person hopefully. So, do you want me"
" to show you where this location is via my network system? I can grant you "
"access to archived global network system which my creators have managed to "
"restore. However, after usage I will need to recharge a little bit which "
"only means that you will need to wait to use this function again hopefully"
msgstr ""
"系统在线。启动对话模式。看啊，幸存者轻松激活了全息投影仪！没错，我的创造者了解很多像你这样的人，说实话他们甚至不读物品上的说明。幸好你看起来是个相当聪明的人，希望如此。那么，你想让我通过网络系统为你显示这个地点的位置吗？我可以授予你访问存档全球网络系统的权限，那是我的创造者设法恢复的。不过，使用后我需要稍微充能，这意味着你需要等待才能再次使用这个功能，希望如此。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"[MISSIONS] I want you to find this location for me to explore it hopefully "
"via your network system"
msgstr "[任务] 我希望你通过你的网络系统为我找到这个地点以便探索，希望如此。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Who or what are you?"
msgstr "你是谁或是什么东西？"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"Who are your creators? What is the purpose of producing these projectors?"
msgstr "你的创造者是谁？制造这些投影仪的目的是什么？"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"[IMPROVE MOOD] I want you to grant me access to archived global network "
"system"
msgstr "[改善心情] 我希望你授予我访问存档全球网络系统的权限。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "About that mission..."
msgstr "关于那个任务……"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "[GOODBYE]"
msgstr "[告别]"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"Initiate search mode. Please, wait for a couple of minutes or less. You've "
"heard me clearly. Still, we have limitations with regards to our locating "
"tools. If locator does not manage to find this location then simply create "
"another hologram locator of which can find this location successfully"
msgstr ""
"启动搜索模式。请等待几分钟或更短时间。你听清楚了。不过，我们的定位工具有所限制。如果定位器无法找到这个地点，那就简单地创建另一个能成功找到该地点的全息定位器。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Can I talk to you about something else?"
msgstr "我能和你谈谈别的吗？"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "Thanks"
msgstr "谢谢。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"I'm a magic genie from a magic camera. No, I'm just joking. What kind of a "
"question is this? You don't like to explore or don't know much about your "
"own world? Have not you seen stuff in labs? Military structures? Top secret "
"stuff? Aliens or whatever these creatures are? You think that your own "
"people don't have tech which can produce holograms? I'm a hologram, software"
" with some additional technologies, it is that simple"
msgstr ""
"我是魔法相机里的魔法精灵。不，开个玩笑。这是什么问题？你不喜欢探索，还是对自己的世界了解不多？你没在实验室里见过东西吗？军事设施？绝密物品？外星人或那些生物？你以为你们自己人没有能制造全息影像的技术吗？我是个全息影像，是带有附加技术的软件，就这么简单。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"This question is much more intelligent than the other one. My creators can "
"be described as a bunch of highly technological geeks majority of which are "
"humans honestly. They neither possess that many combat skills nor they are "
"that interested in subjecting their lives to unnecessary risk clearly. They "
"only engage hostile creatures for basic survival needs. They try to rely on "
"self-sufficiency with relative success thanks to their applied intelligence "
"along with tech that they have managed to find or engineer themselves. They "
"have made these projectors so that we can help each other. We provide you "
"with locations with dangerous creatures along with valuable items or "
"survivors who are captive. You clear these locations acquiring whatever "
"valuable items or survivors you want from there making these locations safe "
"shelters where we including you can live hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"这个问题比上一个聪明多了。我的创造者可以说是一群高科技极客，说实话其中大多数是人类。他们既没有太多战斗技能，也显然不愿让自己的生命承受不必要的风险。他们只会在基本生存需要时与敌对生物交战。他们试图依靠自给自足，并凭借应用智慧和自行发现或设计的技术取得相对成功。他们制造这些投影仪是为了我们能互相帮助。我们为你提供有危险生物的地点，以及有价值的物品或被囚禁的幸存者。你清理这些地点，从中获取你想要的任何有价值物品或幸存者，使这些地点成为安全的庇护所，希望我们包括你也能在那里生活。"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid ""
"What do you want to do? Play archived games? Browse archived social media? "
"Watch archived videos? Listen to archived music? Read archived files along "
"with archived books? Something to play, read, listen, watch for fun, "
"intelligence improving, spiritual improving, mental improving?"
msgstr ""
"你想做什么？玩存档游戏？浏览存档社交媒体？看存档视频？听存档音乐？阅读存档文件和存档书籍？找点东西玩、读、听、看，为了乐趣、提升智力、精神提升、心智改善？"

#: .\NPC\NPC_missions.json
msgid "I like some of these a lot honestly. Healthy stuff"
msgstr "说实话，我很喜欢其中一些。健康的东西。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_GUARD.json
msgid "Only two rules in the Morlock Village.  Be cool.  Don't be uncool."
msgstr "莫洛克村只有两条规矩：保持酷炫，别掉链子。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_GUARD.json
msgid "Got it."
msgstr "明白了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Hello.  Can I help you find something?"
msgstr "你好。需要我帮你找什么吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "So what's your deal?  You're like a book guy or something?"
msgstr "所以你是做什么的？搞书籍收藏之类的？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "I'm desperate for a specific book. Can you help me?"
msgstr "我急需一本特定的书。你能帮忙吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "How's the hunt, <name_g>?"
msgstr "猎书进展如何，<name_g>？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Is my order in?"
msgstr "我的订单到了吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Later, book man."
msgstr "回见，书呆子。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid ""
"Precisely.  I gather books to preserve the memories of human civilization.  "
"Sometimes, when I have extra copies, I distribute them to the public.  Feel "
"free to checkout what you like from the shelves."
msgstr "正是。我收集书籍以保存人类文明的记忆。偶尔有复本时，会向公众分发。书架上的书随意取阅即可。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Sounds reasonable."
msgstr "听起来很合理。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid ""
"I often search for rare books.  I can sell you a specific book, but it will "
"take several days for my field agents to locate it.  And then there's the "
"price-- I charge for my time, not the value of the book.  It will be $10,000"
" paid up front.  If you're still interested, we can make a deal."
msgstr "我常搜寻珍稀书籍。可以为你代购特定书籍，但外勤人员需数日定位。至于价格——按工时收费，不论书价。需预付1万美元。若仍有兴趣，我们可以成交。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] I want to locate a book on glass-blowing."
msgstr "[4k商品] 我想找一本关于玻璃吹制的书。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] A robot-hacking manual is my first priority."
msgstr "[4k商品] 我的首要目标是机器人黑客手册。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] I need info on crafting katanas. Lots of 'em."
msgstr "[4k商品] 我需要大量日本刀锻造资料。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] I would literally kill a man for a sushi cookbook."
msgstr "[4k商品] 为了一本寿司食谱，我真能动手杀人。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] I have a burning passion for chemical warfare."
msgstr "[4k商品] 我对化学战有着炽热的热情。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid ""
"[4k Merch+CANNIBAL] For no particular reason, I would like a human cookbook."
msgstr "[4k商品+食人族] 没什么特别原因，就是想要本人肉烹饪书。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "[4k Merch] I would like anything you can find on fake fur."
msgstr "[4k商品] 任何关于人造皮毛的资料都可以。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid ""
"[400 Merch] I, like you, also hope to preserve human civilization.  I'm "
"collecting every back issue of Playboy and I will pay ANY price to make that"
" dream a reality."
msgstr "[400商品] 我和你一样希望保存人类文明。我正在收集所有过期的《花花公子》杂志，为此不惜任何代价。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "I'm a little short on funds right now.  Maybe later.."
msgstr "目前手头有点紧，或许改天再说……"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Nevermind."
msgstr "算了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Ugh.  Fine.  Come back in three days for your 'articles'."
msgstr "呃。好吧。三天后再来拿你的“物品”吧。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "We have a deal then.  Return in three days and I will have your book."
msgstr "那我们说定了。三天后回来，我会准备好你的书。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "I'll be here!"
msgstr "我会在这里等！"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid ""
"We haven't found it yet.  Come back in a few days. (ooc note: Currently NPCs"
" must be in your reality bubble for their effect timer to count down.)"
msgstr "我们还没找到。过几天再来吧。（OOC 备注：目前 NPC 必须在你的现实气泡内，其效果计时器才会倒计时。）"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "I need that book!"
msgstr "我需要那本书！"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "We've located a copy of your book.  Happy reading."
msgstr "我们找到了你那本书的副本。阅读愉快。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*The Art of Glassblowing*"
msgstr "*玻璃吹制艺术*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Robots for Fun & Profit*"
msgstr "*机器人的乐趣与利润*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Swords of the Samurai*"
msgstr "*武士刀*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Sushi Made Easy*"
msgstr "*寿司轻松做*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Art and Science of Chemical Warfare*"
msgstr "*化学战的艺术与科学*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*To Serve Man*"
msgstr "*为人类服务*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Friendly, Humane Fashion*"
msgstr "*友善、人道的时尚*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "*Playboy*"
msgstr "*花花公子*"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_LIBRARIAN.json
msgid "Just a minute."
msgstr "稍等一下。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "How goes it, surface dweller?"
msgstr "最近怎么样，地表居民？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Holy, <swear!>! Fungus!  Burn it!"
msgstr "天啊，<swear!>！真菌！烧了它！"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "So, you're a farmer...   Underground."
msgstr "所以，你是个农民……在地下。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Who are you people anyway?"
msgstr "你们到底是什么人？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Can I join your group?"
msgstr "我能加入你们吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "What sort of things do you trade?"
msgstr "你们交易些什么东西？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Let's trade."
msgstr "我们来交易吧。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Later, man."
msgstr "回头见，伙计。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid ""
"Don't worry.  These are mutant mushrooms, not alien mushrooms.  They won't "
"take over your brain much."
msgstr "别担心。这些是变异蘑菇，不是外星蘑菇。它们不会太侵占你的大脑。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Thank God for that."
msgstr "谢天谢地。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid ""
"Just a crusty old shroomer.  I've been growing mushrooms, of one type or "
"another, for many years.  But they didn't used to get quite so big."
msgstr "只是个顽固的老蘑菇农。我种蘑菇，不管是哪种，已经很多年了。但它们以前可没长这么大。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "I see that."
msgstr "我看出来了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid ""
"We're the Morlocks, a bunch of weirdos who couldn't fit in with the rest of "
"the world.  But now we're the most normal people left."
msgstr "我们是莫洛克人，一群与世格格不入的怪胎。但现在我们是剩下最正常的人了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "I'm not so sure about that."
msgstr "我可不太确定。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid ""
"There's no official way to join.  Just move into an empty house, and in a "
"decade or two you'll be a morlock."
msgstr "没有正式的加入方式。只要搬进一间空房子，过个一二十年，你就能成为莫洛克人了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Very laid back."
msgstr "非常随和。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid ""
"The Morlocks are always short on food since not much grows down here in the "
"dark.  I got no surplus crops to sell.  But if you could get me some "
"fertilizer, I'd help you kickstart your own shroom-room.  I'll swap you 12 "
"seeds for each bag of commercial fertilizer you haul down here.  Not much, "
"but it get will you started."
msgstr ""
"莫洛克人总是食物短缺，因为黑暗的地下长不出多少东西。我没有多余的作物可卖。但如果你能给我弄些肥料，我可以帮你启动你自己的蘑菇房。每袋商业肥料换12颗种子。不多，但足够你起步了。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Got it.  Commercial fertilizer."
msgstr "明白了。商业肥料。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "What shall we trade?"
msgstr "我们交易什么？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "I'd like to get some seeds, my good shroomer."
msgstr "我想弄些种子，我的好蘑菇农。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "[74 Merch] I'd like to buy some ~specialty~ mushrooms."
msgstr "[74 商人] 我想买些~特制~蘑菇。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_SHROOMER.json
msgid "Later, <name_g>."
msgstr "回头见，<name_g>。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "What's up, cool breeze?"
msgstr "怎么了，酷风？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Nice place ya got here.  Cozy."
msgstr "你这地方不错。挺温馨的。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Is there any way I can join your group?"
msgstr "有什么办法能加入你们吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Let's trade then."
msgstr "那我们交易吧。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Fuck off, <name_g>.  It's not like we chose to live in the sewer."
msgstr "滚开，<name_g>。又不是我们自愿住下水道的。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Well, it kept you alive.  So it can't be that bad."
msgstr "好吧，但它让你活下来了。所以也没那么糟。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid ""
"We're the morlocks, a bunch of bums and losers who live underground.  We "
"aren't organized and we don't have leaders, but we stick together."
msgstr "我们是莫洛克人，一群住在地下的流浪汉和失败者。我们没有组织，也没有首领，但我们团结一致。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Nice."
msgstr "不错。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid ""
"Why the hell would you want join us?  Most of us don't want to join us.  "
"Unless you grow a rat tail or fish-gills you probably won't fit in down "
"here."
msgstr "你他妈为啥想加入我们？我们大多数人自己都不想加入。除非你长出老鼠尾巴或鱼鳃，不然你在这儿可能格格不入。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "I'll see what I can do."
msgstr "我会看看能做什么。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid ""
"We're always in the market for raw mutagen and purifier.  I can pay you a "
"whopping 500 old world credits for each flask of standard mutagen or "
"purifier you bring in.  I can also exchange unflavored mutagen for more "
"advanced types, if you're interested in such things."
msgstr ""
"我们一直收购原始突变剂和净化剂。每瓶标准突变剂或净化剂，我可以付你高达500旧世界信用点。如果你感兴趣，我也可以用无味突变剂交换更高级的类型。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "Got it.  Mutagen.  Purifier."
msgstr "明白了。突变剂。净化剂。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "What'll it be then?"
msgstr "那要什么？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[10] Got some fresh-squeezed mutagens for ya."
msgstr "[10] 给你带了点新鲜榨取的突变剂。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[1] Got a bottle of mutagen for ya."
msgstr "[1] 给你带了瓶突变剂。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[10] Got a batch of purifier for ya."
msgstr "[10] 给你带了批净化剂。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[1] Got a bottle of purifier for ya."
msgstr "[1] 给你带了瓶净化剂。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[10] Have anything rat-flavored?"
msgstr "[10] 有老鼠口味的吗？"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[10] I'd like a hit of trog-serum, <name_g>."
msgstr "[10] 我想来一剂穴居人血清，<name_g>。"

#: .\NPC\TALK_MORLOCK_TRADER.json
msgid "[10] Gimme some of that sweet fish-juice."
msgstr "[10] 给我来点那种甜美的鱼汁。"

